	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Tue, Oct 9th 5:37 AM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent<span id=notbold>[5.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Twinking is giving a lower level character equipment and weapons that said character would be unable to acquire on his/her own.&nbsp;&nbsp;As a level 7 monk, you're likely to be earning coppers and silvers - perhaps the occasional gold piece - by looting the mobs you kill.  On occasion, you might be able to sell things like spider silks, high quality bear pelts, and deathfist belts for platinum pieces.  So, with some luck and perseverance, you might manage to get yourself in to the tens of platinum, or perhaps as much as a hundred platinum.  Clearly, you could not afford to have a pair of Canes of the Tranquil, an FBSS, azure sleeves, a froglok crown, etc etc.  If you had a friend or a higher level character that passed on either money or equipment to you, you'd be a twink.<br>&nbsp;<br>Keyeluke<br>Member of Tenacity - Druzzil Ro<br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=27415" target=_new>http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=27415</a></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
