	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f10025393323298><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=3&mid=10025393323298>RE: MoNeY!</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=3&mid=10025393323298#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=35651><span id=Guru>Keyeluke</span></a>, <span id=Guru>Guru</span><br><span id=notbold>670 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Mon, Oct 8th 7:08 AM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent<span id=notbold>[5.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Well, don't expect to make any money till you level up some more.&nbsp;&nbsp;You have a full set of cured silk at lvl 5 - that's far better than most people do with their first characters.  Just kill, kill, kill, and level, level, level.  As you level up, get into the habit of saving things like spiderling and spider silks, quality pelts, bone chips, and other things that player characters buy.  Get a small sewing kit and combine the silks into threads and swatches - you can get the first points in tailoring that way - it never fails.  A stack of swatches can go for 50p on Druzzil to the right player.  A HQ bear pelt goes for 40p.  Just pay attention to the /auction channel and see what it is people buy and sell - I used to sell all my pelts and silks to the merchant, and now realize how much money I let slip through my fingers.<br><br>One thing to repeat.  You're level 5!  Get out and fight!  Level up a ways - you're not gonna make any real money till you're higher level anyway, so go kill stuff.<br>&nbsp;<br>Keyeluke<br>Member of Tenacity - Druzzil Ro<br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=27415" target=_new>http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=27415</a></td></tr>
